      {
        "season": 11,
        "twist": "Cursed Island begins as a survival test and becomes a study in how trust breaks under pressure. The pre-merge is defined by sabotage, swaps, exposed idols, and tribes that never fully stabilize: Ashley is framed, Drew is discarded, Will is betrayed, Eureka is rocked out, Wix is exiled by emissary power, Grett detonates half the game on her way out, Nick exposes alliances, and Sterling falls to a fractured Teal endgame. At the merge, no alliance survives first contact with public voting, idol insurance, or personal grudges. Ellie weaponizes a Super Idol, Dan loses the one read he needed, Jake's heart becomes both shield and target, and Fiore's Second Life Amulet rewrites the final six. Through it all, Miriam and Thom build a bond so visible it should destroy them, but instead it carries them to the finale. The season ends not with a jury speech, but with a volcanic race where Miriam weaponizes that bond one final time and steals the million from the person who trusted her most."
      }
    ]
